    "22": {
      "play": "I mean, that married her, alack, good man!",
      "notes": [
        "alacke good man] STAUNTON (Athenæum, 14 June, '73) thinks that Capell's punctuation, generally followed, which places this exclamation between dashes, and with an exclamation mark, appears to imply that 'Posthumus is to be commiserated for having married Imogen!' We ought, therefore, to read, 'I mean that married her—alack, good man, And therefore banish'd!—'—HUDSON adopted the suggestion."
      ]
