    "230": {
      "play": "Go see my lord aboard. For this time leave me.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "231": {
      "play": "[They exit.]",
      "notes": [
        "Exeunt] SHERMAN (p. 10): Evidently Shakespeare is not yet fully at work. Neither in this scene nor in the preceding does his hand suggest the cunning that it has known in most earlier plays. Particularly this plan of character contrasts, which presents first a scene of Imogen, and then of Cloten, and then of Imogen again, is unexampled in all his work elsewhere."
      ]
    }
