    "10": {
      "play": "FIRST LORD: Hurt him? His body’s a passable carcass if",
      "notes": [
        "passable] SCHMIDT (Lex.): Affording free passage. 10, 11. if he bee not hurt ... if it be not hurt] Can any man lay his hand on his honest heart and say this needless repetition sounds like Shakespeare?—ED. 12, 13. His Steele . . . Towne] DELIUS: In order to spare him, Posthumus’s steel sneaked roundabout Cloten’s body, like a debtor trying to avoid his creditors. THISELTON (p. 8): In An Account of James the First’s Visit in 1615 to the University of Cambridge, given in the Appendix to Hawkins’ edition of Ignoramus, we read that certain ‘Jesuits or priests, being to be conveyed from London to Wisbich castle, were not suffered to come thorough Cambridge, but by the Sheriff carried over the backe side of the town to Cambridge castle.’"
      ]
