      "notes": [
        "But he added . . . ground] WALKER (Crit., iii, 316) queries whether the stage-direction at the head of this Scene should not be, 'Enter Cloten and three Lords'; and, because he doubts that 'Puppies' refers to the First Lord and Cloten, he gives this line 17 to the Third Lord. [I cannot see how this addition to the group mends matters, or what objection there is to calling Cloten, or the First Lord either, a 'puppy.'—ED.]"
      ]
