    "28": {
      "play": "SECOND LORD, aside  If it be a sin to make a true election,",
      "notes": [
        "election] WHITE (ed. i.): The allusion plainly is to the doctrine of election held by the Calvinists. [I think this is doubtful. The Calvinistic 'election' is a prerogative of God; man cannot 'make it.' 'Election' is here used, I think, in its ordinary sense. See Craig's note, I, ii, 84.—ED.]"
      ]
