      "notes": [
        "of a Gnat, to ayre] In reading or speaking, the slight pause after ‘Gnat,’ indicated by the comma in the Folio, should not be overlooked.—CAPELL, I am sorry to say, was the first to remove this comma, and he has been almost uniformly followed by succeeding editors. Of course, as far as the mere construction of the sentence is concerned, the punctuation of the Folio is erroneous.—ED."
      ]
