        "makes him] JOHNSON: In the sense in which we say, This will make or mar you. 11, 12. both without, and within] DOWDEN refers to ‘All that is out of door most rich,’ etc.—I, vii, 20. Possibly an equally apt comparison lies in, ‘So faire an Outward, and such stuffe Within Endowes a man, but hee.’—I, i, 32. 14, 15. as hee] DOWDEN: Perhaps this refers to Iachimo, and if so, ‘the sun’ must stand ironically for Posthumus; but ‘he’ may be Posthumus, and the meaning may be, we had as many eagles as true of breed as he. Compare 3 Hen. VI: II, i, 91, 92: ‘Nay, if thou be that princely eagle’s bird, Show thy descent by gazing ’gainst the sun.’ [It seems to me that ‘he’ must refer to ‘I have seen him in France,’ and that Dowden’s paraphrase is just.—ED.]"
