      "notes": [
        "a Couenant] RUSHTON (Sh. a Lawyer, p. 23): The Covenant Shakespeare refers to is, according to the quaint description of Thomas Wood (Inst. of the Laws of England, ed. ii, p. 228), ‘agreements made by deed in writing, by the consent of two or more, to do, or not to do,’ and not the covenants (conventiones) which are clauses of agreement contained in a deed."
