    "10": {
      "play": "Which seasons comfort. Who may this be? Fie!",
      "notes": [
        "Which seasons comfort] WARBURTON: These words are equivocal,",
        "Fye.] CAPELL: There is much expression in ‘Fie!’—RANN: On such intrusion.—DEIGHTON: An exclamation of surprise.—WYATT: Imogen is sorry to have her solitude broken in upon.—PORTER and CLARKE: Does she exclaim at herself for hoping for news?—DOWDEN: An outbreak of impatience at the interruption of her solitary thoughts. [Hence, it is clear that, where our betters disagree, we are all at liberty to give to this ‘Fie!’ whatever intonation or interpretation our mood suggests.—ED.]"
      ]
    },
    "11": {
      "play": "[Enter Pisanio and Iachimo.]",
      "notes": []
