      "play": "Not so allured to feed.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "56": {
      "play": "IMOGEN: What is the matter, trow?",
      "notes": [
        "trow] LETTSON (Fool-note to Walker, Crit., i, 79): This apparently answers to the modern I wonder. [See ‘What meanes the foole trow?’—Much Ado, III, iv, 55 (of this ed.), where ‘trow’ has the same meaning as in the present passage, which is there referred to.] 55-57. The Cloyed will: . . . running: Rauenning] CAPELL (p. 106): The word ‘desire’ has crept in no one knows how, to the utter perversion of sense and metre: by discarding it, and placing the parenthesis properly, this speech is perfected now, for the suppli al of thing after ‘that’ is obvious to every one."
      ]
