    "146": {
      "play": "With pity that doth make me sick. A lady",
      "notes": []
    },
    "147": {
      "play": "So fair, and fastened to an empery",
      "notes": [
        "Emperie] BRADLEY (N. E. D., s. v., Empery 2. a.): The territory ruled by an Emperor. b. In wider sense: The territory of an absolute or powerful ruler. [As here, probably.]"
      ]
