        "a mornings] What scholarly reason can be given for changing this into o’mornings? especially here, where, if it be an illiterate pronunciation, it is in character?—ED. 14, 15. it will penetrate] The present passage is the only instance given by MURRAY (N. E. D., s. v.) of the intransitive use of this verb. He defines it: 'To touch the heart, affect the feelings.'"
