    "37": {
      "play": "POSTHUMUS: I hope the briefness of your answer made",
      "notes": [
        "Post.] CAPELL (p. 108): No thinking person will ever be of opinion that Posthumus could be the asker of such a question as this. He has that in his hand which engages him wholly; and his eagerness to know the contents of it appears in his very hasty perusal even now that he is eased of this speech, for the time allowed is so short that we must conceive it helped by the action. [The credit of this just change was assumed by STEEVENS; it was attributed to him by MALONE.]"
      ]
