      "notes": [
        "Is left vtender'd] BOSWELL-STONE (p. 9): This pretension to tribute arose when Caesar, after defeating Cassibelan, blockaded the residue of the British levies, so that—[Hol. i. H. E. 30]—‘Cassibelane in the end was forced to fall to a composition, in couenanting to paie a yearelie tribute of three thousand pounds.’"
      ]
    },
