        "to Prince it] For other examples of this indefinite use of ‘it’ after nouns or words that are not generally used as verbs, to give them the force of verbs, such as ‘Foot it featly,’ Temp., I, ii, 380; ‘I’ll queen it no inch further,’ Wint. Tale, IV, iv, 460, etc., see ABBOTT, § 226."
      ]
