    "35": {
      "play": "pander to her dishonor and equally to me disloyal.",
      "notes": [
        "disloyall] LADY MARTIN (p. 190): My pen stops here. I know not how to write. Such a charge as that letter contains, to meet the eye of such a creature! She has begun to read, full of apprehension for her husband's safety, and from his hand she now receives her deathblow. As the last word drops from her lips, her head bows in silence over the writing, and her body shrinks as if some mighty rock had crushed her with its weight. These few words have sufficed to blight, to blacken, and to wither her whole life. The wonder is that she ever rises. I used to feel tied to the earth."
      ]
    },
