    "105": {
      "play": "Of princely fellows, shalt hereafter find",
      "notes": [
        "Princely Fellowes] Malone: One of the same fellowships or rank with myself.—Collier pronounced ‘Fellows’ ‘absurd,’ and in his second and third editions adopted the reading of his MS. followers.—Anon. (Blackwood, Oct., 1853, p. 471): Imogen means princely equals. This is undoubted. Posthumus was beneath her in rank; yet, for his sake, she had declined the proposals of suitors as high-born as herself."
      ]
