        "we’l brouz on that] MURRAY (N. E. D.): To browse properly implies the cropping of scanty vegetation—said of goats, deer, cattle. [The present is the earliest instance recorded by Murray of the use of ‘browse’ in a figurative sense. If this prove correct, it is perhaps worthy of remark that even now, when use and wont have familiarized us with fanciful uses of the term, to speak of ‘browsing on cold meat’ would raise a smile, and that this smile must have broadened into a laugh when, for the first time, a Globe audience heard this huntsman’s word put into a huntsman’s mouth, and thus drolly applied.—Ed.]"
