    "43": {
      "play": "’Tis the ninth hour o’ th’ morn.",
      "notes": [
        "'Tis the ninth hour o' th' Morne] CAPELL: As Belarius utters these words he turns to a part of the cave and takes down some of their hunting instruments, reaching one to Arviragus, which is the occasion of the words, 'So please you, Sir,' the reaching being linked with a call. [Dr Johnson, borrowing from Prospero's speech to Caliban, said that if ‘Capell had come to him, he would have endowed his purposes with words.’—ED.]"
      ]
