    "47": {
      "play": "ARVIRAGUS, as Cadwal  You health.—So please you, sir.",
      "notes": [
        "So please you Sir] TYRWHITT: I cannot relish this courtly phrase from the mouth of Arviragus. It should rather, I think, begin Imogen's speech. [See preceding note.]—WALKER (Crit., iii, 326): Point, ‘So please you, sir—’ Arviragus is speaking to Belarius. [See Capell’s preceding note, wherein he anticipates Walker.]"
      ]
