    "106": {
      "play": "He is but one. You and my brother search",
      "notes": [
        "What Companies] WALKER, in his valuable Article on the frequent interpolation and omission of s in the Folio, quotes (Crit., i, 225) this line and asks, 'Why the plural? A little below we have “No company’s abroad.” And again, “—what company Discover you abroad?”’ DYCE quotes Walker, without comment. I think the present example hardly within the scope of Walker’s Article; the verb shows that, whatever be the reason, the plural is intentional, and ought we then to change it? SCHMIDT (Lex.) gives it as equivalent to ‘people.’—ED."
      ]
    },
