      "notes": [
        "Is Cadwall mad?] THISELTON (p. 39): Guiderius thinks that Arviragus has set the ‘ingenuous instrument’ going either to celebrate his (G.’s) victory over Cloten or by way of threnody for Cloten’s death."
      ]
    },
    "284": {
      "play": "[Enter Arviragus as Cadwal, with Imogen as dead,]",
      "notes": [
        "with Imogen dead] Capell was afflicted with a chronic propensity to insert stage directions. Possibly in his secret soul he believed that in him the world had lost a consummate actor. However this may be, he certainly had no"
      ]
