      "notes": []
    },
    "310": {
      "play": "His arms thus leagued. I thought he slept, and put",
      "notes": [
        "His armes thus leagu’d] SCHMIDT (Lex.) defines ‘leagu’d’ as ‘joined, folded together.’—I suppose across the breast. This example and this use of the verb seems to have escaped both WHITNEY (Century Dict.) and MURRAY (N. E. D.)."
      ]
