        "The Scepter, Learning, etc.] JOHNSON: The Poet’s sentiment seems to have been this: All human excellence is equally subject to the stroke of death; neither the power of kings, nor the science of scholars, nor the art of those whose immediate study is the prolongation of life, can protect them from the final destiny of man."
