      "notes": [
        "We haue done our obsequies] JOHNSON: For the obsequies of Fidele a song was written by my unhappy friend, Mr William Collins of Chichester, a man of uncommon learning and abilities. I shall give it a place at the end in honour of his memory. [See Appendix.]"
