      "notes": [
        "I tremble still with feare] ECCLES: She seems, at pronouncing these words, to have risen from the ground, and stood somewhat apart from the body. 384, 385. as small a drop of pitie As a Wren’s eye] It is ‘sacred pity’ that ‘engenders’ drops in eyes (As You Like It, II, vii, 123), and Imogen pleads but for a drop in the smallest of eyes.—ED."
      ]
