        "weedes] That is, clothes, as in Shakespeare passim. They are referred to again in ‘habits,’ line 32. 31-35. Let me . . . more within] The vulgar, discordant note struck in these lines, with their braggart tone, from a heart-broken man whose only prayer was a death unknown, never came from the hand that wrote what precedes it.—ED."
      ]
