    "60": {
      "play": "POSTHUMUS: Nay, do not wonder at it. You are made",
      "notes": [
        "Nay, do not wonder at it] JOHNSON: Posthumus first bids him not wonder, then tells him in another mode of reproach that wonder was all that he was made for.—VAUGHAN (p. 517): Perhaps there are not two modes of reproach, but a command and a reproachful expostulation of its necessity. If ‘you are made,’ etc., were right, I would read: ‘They do not wonder,’ etc. But I very much prefer to amend the end of the line than the beginning, thus: ‘You are mad,’ etc."
      ]
