      "play": "And then a mind put in ’t, either our brags",
      "notes": [
        "then a minde put in’t] VAUGHAN (p. 540): ‘Mind’ I take to mean not mere life, but ‘all mental qualities,’ such, for instance, as that more than Dianaic"
      ]
