    "232": {
      "play": "Were cracked of kitchen trulls, or his description",
      "notes": [
        "crak’d] SCHMIDT (Lex., s. v. crack): To talk in a blustering manner.—MURRAY (N. E. D., s. v. crack, 6.): To talk big, boast. [Thus also, WRIGHT, E. Dialect. Dict.]",
        "Trulles] Drabs, sluts, slatterns."
