    "236": {
      "play": "He spake of her as Dian had hot dreams",
      "notes": [
        "as] See ‘As you did meane,’ line 505, below; and for other examples of ‘as’ equivalent to as if, see Abbott, § 107."
      ]
    },
    "237": {
      "play": "And she alone were cold; whereat I, wretch,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "238": {
      "play": "Made scruple of his praise and wagered with him",
      "notes": [
        "Made scruple] ONIONS (Gloss., s. v. scruple): That is, hesitate to believe or admit, to doubt."
      ]
    },
    "239": {
      "play": "Pieces of gold ’gainst this, which then he wore",
      "notes": []
    },
    "240": {
      "play": "Upon his honored finger, to attain",
      "notes": [
        "honour’d finger] His finger was honoured by bearing on it a token of such love and devotion."
      ]
