      "notes": [
        "sweet’st] For other examples of similar contraction, see ABBOTT, § 473."
      ]
    },
    "452": {
      "play": "The benediction of these covering heavens",
      "notes": []
    },
    "453": {
      "play": "Fall on their heads like dew, for they are worthy",
      "notes": []
    },
    "454": {
      "play": "To inlay heaven with stars.      He weeps.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "455": {
      "play": "CYMBELINE: Thou weep’st and speak’st.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "456": {
      "play": "The service that you three have done is more",
      "notes": []
    },
