    "527": {
      "play": "The soldier that did company these three",
      "notes": []
    },
    "528": {
      "play": "In poor beseeming; ’twas a fitment for",
      "notes": [
        "a fitment] According to Bartlett’s Concordance this word is used—I’ll not say by Shakespeare—in only one other place in the Third Folio. It occurs in Pericles, IV, iii, 6, in the sense of what is befitting, which is, possibly, the exact sense of the present passage, where Posthumus’s forlorn or poor beseeming befitted his purpose.—Ed."
      ]
    },
    "529": {
      "play": "The purpose I then followed. That I was he,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "530": {
      "play": "Speak, Iachimo. I had you down and might",
      "notes": []
    },
    "531": {
      "play": "Have made you finish.",
      "notes": [
        "finish] That is, die. See ‘Were present when she finish’d,’ line 47 of this scene."
      ]
    },
    "532": {
      "play": "IACHIMO, kneeling  I am down again,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "533": {
      "play": "But now my heavy conscience sinks my knee,",
      "notes": [
        "sinkes my knee] Lest we should fail to comprehend the meaning of"
      ]
    },
    "534": {
      "play": "As then your force did. Take that life, beseech you,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "535": {
      "play": "Which I so often owe; but your ring first,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "536": {
      "play": "And here the bracelet of the truest princess",
      "notes": []
    },
    "537": {
      "play": "That ever swore her faith.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "538": {
      "play": "He holds out the ring and bracelet.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "539": {
      "play": "POSTHUMUS: Kneel not to me.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "540": {
      "play": "The power that I have on you is to spare you;",
      "notes": []
    },
    "541": {
      "play": "The malice towards you to forgive you. Live",
      "notes": []
    },
    "542": {
      "play": "And deal with others better.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "543": {
      "play": "CYMBELINE: Nobly doomed.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "544": {
      "play": "We’ll learn our freeness of a son-in-law:",
      "notes": []
    },
    "545": {
      "play": "Pardon’s the word to all.  Iachimo rises.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "546": {
      "play": "ARVIRAGUS, to Posthumus  You holp us, sir,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "547": {
      "play": "As you did mean indeed to be our brother.",
      "notes": [
        "As you did meane] That is, as if. See line 215, above, or Abbott, § 107."
      ]
